This paper is likely to belong to the arXiv CS sub-category of cs.CL (Computation and Language) as it deals with the representation of words in natural language processing. It could also belong to cs.LG (Machine Learning) as it discusses unsupervised feature learning and the structure of latent spaces. Additionally, it could be categorized under cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence) as it deals with the development of powerful latent representations of words. It may also fall under cs.SI (Social and Information Networks) as it explores the properties of language networks. Finally, it could be categorized under cs.NE (Neural and Evolutionary Computing) as it discusses techniques for creating language networks from learned features.
